29/04/2011
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Foreign ministers of Italy, Greece, Israel, Malta and Cyprus will gather on Friday (April 29th) in Limassol for an informal meeting to discuss immigration issues.
Bulgaria will be represented by a deputy foreign minister.
The talks will focus on the influx of illegal immigrants from North Africa and the Middle East due to the turmoil there and ways to deal with the problem.
(Darik, BNR, The Jerusalem Post - 29/04/11)
